itter in the middle also makes your backfield, including your goalie, totally useless most of the time, which is why they have incredibly low levels.<br><br>RD Lakkam L22<br>PA 35 AT 21 BL 13<br>Heavy hitter who can dish the ball if need be. Great for setting up my shooters.<br><br>LB Judda L24<br>EN 27 AT 24<br>PA 28 BL 14<br>Another heavy hitter.<br><br>K Nimrook L23<br>CA 24<br>Nothing is getting by him. In most games, nothing gets to him.<br><br><br>The computer is just totally moronic in this game. They have absolutely no strategy. Given a clear path to the goal with their best shooter, they will back out, force a concentration, and pass it to the other side of the arena, where I then take the ball and score. The drawbacks to this team is that I never learn any shooting techniques because the computer rarely gets a shot off, and I've already learned all the tackling and passing skills. The keys to this team are Brother and Berrik, in my opinion, the absolute best players in the game by a long margin. They have no weaknesses. <p><img src="http://www.spikescafe.com/shellt.gif"> <a href="http://www.spikescafe.com/">3D Spike</a> (Entered a strange dimension thanks to X 51 K)<BR><table width=464 height=64 border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td><img src="http://www.spikescafe.com/sig/top.gif"><br><img src="http://www.spikescafe.com/sig/1.gif"><a href="http://www.7hat.com/posting/"><img src="http://www.spikescafe.com/sig/2.gif" border=0></a><img src="http://www.spikescafe.com/sig/3.gif"><a href="http://www.spikescafe.com/crit/crit.htm"><img src="http://www.spikescafe.com/sig/4.gif" border=0></a><img src="http://www.spikescafe.com/sig/5.gif"><ahref="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm27"target="_newbrow"><img src="http://www.spikescafe.com/sig/6.gif" border=0></a><img src="http://www.spikescafe.com/sig/7.gif"><ahref="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm18"target="_newbrow"><img src="http://www.spikescafe.com/sig/8.gif" 